Today's the day - happy Virtual Charter Day 2020! We're going LIVE on Facebook at 11:30AM, and we can't wait for you to join us! Follow these quick instructions to tune in and share our live post with YOUR friends, school Facebook page audience, etc.

Visit our MI Charters Facebook page around 11:30AM, when we'll go LIVE for the big program. We'll wait for about 5 minutes before getting started so everyone can tune in.
Once you find the video on our page, click the "Share" option. Either select "Share Now (Friends)" or to share to your school's Facebook page select "More Options" then "Share to a Page" and select your school's page.
Be sure to have your school swag on, and be ready to post a photo showing it off, along with a message about why you LOVE your charter school, in the comments!

PBIS Appreciation Tree.

Our #PBIS character trait focus for the month of November is Appreciation. Appreciation is an awareness of how special, lucky unique, and blessed something is. Having appreciation for people and things helps children maintain and support relationships and feel connected to a caring community. In order for young school age children to learn to be appreciative, we should teach and demonstrate #appreciation.

The next SAT date is December 7, 2019. The registration deadline is November 8, 2019.

If you are a senior who is planning to retake the SAT, I strongly recommend registering for this upcoming test date. Most colleges DO NOT accept SAT scores after December, so now would be the perfect time to get that done.

Please log into your CollegeBoard account to complete your registration.

If you need a fee waiver, please see Ms. Hussain or Ms. Afrah at the counseling office.

**FYI: fee waiver codes DO NOT work after the regular registration period ends. Please make sure you sign up before the late registration begins.

The FAFSA workshop will be held on Wednesday, October 30, 2019 at 9:00 (location to be determined)

Ms. Hussain will send an email with the names of the seniors who are scheduled to attend the workshop that day. PLEASE check your GEE email for the notification.

You are REQUIRED to bring the following information with you in order to complete your application:

1. 2018 tax papers
2. Social security number- student and parents
3. Green card number- student and parents if you aren‚Äôt US citizens yet
4. parents‚Äô date of birth
5. parents‚Äô anniversary

If you already completed a FAFSA application, please forward your confirmation email to Ms. Hussain at hussainb@gee-edu.com

I STRONGLY recommended getting this process completed ASAP. The SOONER your application is submitted the GREATER chances you have for receiving MORE pell grant money.

During your free time, you are always welcome to stop by the counseling office to complete your financial aid application as long as you bring the required information with you. Ms. Hussain and Ms. Afrah will gladly assist you üòä

Wayne State University‚Äôs Heart of Detroit scholarship offers full tuition for students who live in Detroit OR attend a Detroit high school.

Students who meet the admission requirements (3.00 GPA and 920 SAT score) are automatically eligible to be a recipient of this scholarship.

If you have atleast a 3.0 GPA but do not have the sufficient SAT score, you can retake the SAT test on December 6, 2019.

Please see Ms. Hussain in the counseling office for more information about SAT registration and for any inquiries regarding the Heart of Detroit Scholarship.

post_text:
The weather is looking clear, but cool for tomorrow's carnival. Remember to dress in layers, and come join us for the fun! We have 6 different inflatables to play on, a trackless train running from 2-4pm, and Mr. Ajin is coming back to grill hot-dogs and hamburgers at the snack stand.

Kids under 36" (3 feet) tall are $4 each, students and former graduates are $10 each. Parents bringing their younger children are free.
***ALL ADMISSIONS are donated to the Children's Hospital of Michigan Foundation.***

In our snack stand, we'll have a variety of chips, cookies, brownies, fruit snacks, water, pop, and capri-suns to refuel you. (Prices range from .50-$1.00 per item)

Face-paint and Henna art are available for Cash purchase as well.

All proceeds from the sale of food/snacks, face-paint, and henna go back into our NHS budget to fund more student-led school improvement projects, spirit events, and fun!

First day of school!

post_text:
Hello students! We're back to school in a few short weeks, are you ready?

School starts on the 27th - don't wait until the last minute to get your school supplies. At the bare minimum you should have:

-a bookbag to carry all of your books/supplies
-a 1" binder to keep your work organized (some teachers require that you have one for their specific class - so you may need up to 6 binders)
-a notebook for each subject (6 notebooks a semester x 2 semesters is 12 notebooks for the year) - notebooks are on sale at Meijer through August 18th for .25 each.
-2-4 packs of loose leaf paper for completing assignments
-a pack or two of your favorite pens
-a pack of your favorite pencils

We're looking forward to seeing you and having a great year, Frontier Knights!

post_text:
Any students looking for work, please check out this opportunity passed along to you by Mrs. Ammon.

English/Arabic speaker working in construction. No experience necessary. The worker will help an Arabic speaking builder, learning the trade, while assisting in communication with clients and stores.

Requirements:
Ability to communicate in both English and Arabic
Desire to work and gain skills in construction
Physical strength for construction tasks

Significant possibility for growth depending on diligence
Opportunity to learn all aspects of construction leading to a future career.

Call Ken: 586-588-2589

$4 for kids under 4
$10 for children and teens over 4
Parents (with paying child) free!

*Five interactive inflatables!
*Kid's Corner with kid-safe crafts and games with prizes!

*Henna ($2-20) and Face Painting ($2-5) available

*Snack Station with fresh popcorn, cotton candy, and other halal refreshments

All proceeds to benefit the Children's Hospital of Michigan Foundation.
